body:
@michaelmior I resolved the conflicts. I also adapted sub-query.iq in order to re-enable the respective tests. The changes in sub-query.iq are inevitable and they are due to the bug addressed by #847. When #847 gets merged, sub-query.iq will be back to normal but in the meanwhile there is no reason to block this improvement. 

> As an aside, thanks for your patience on this (and other) PRs. We appreciate these contributions!

Thank you too. Any feedback is very much appreciated. I know that it is not easy to keep up with the amount of incoming PRs :)

>Another option is using builder-esque pattern with an options object. I chose the second option because it benefits from being able to have additional options added without further refactoring

Those options do not invalidate each other. Even builder benefits from enum types.


@jacques-n , there's already an enum for `UnknownAs`.
